		<description>My Mito is a good looking car (although not in the league of my Ferrari :-). Mine is a fairly early one and doesn&#039;t benefit from the so called multi air engines that are more powerful and more efficient for the equivalent engine size (1.4 litres in mine).  It&#039;s a good car for it&#039;s type and has excellent fuel economy (at least 40mpg imperial however hard you drive it), but has a terrible ride compared to say the Renault Clio, mainly because I think Alfa have bench marked the Mini as it&#039;s chief rival.  The Mito is sold alongside the 500 in the UK and I don&#039;t see why it wouldn&#039;t so the same in the US, but then I&#039;m not a Fiat product planner :-)

I&#039;ve not tried the Giulietta but would agree that it is the better looking car.</description>
