		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://rockyroadblog.com/?p=605#comment-25</guid>
		<description>A few things, not sure where you got you stats from but I&#039;m pretty certain average mileage in the UK is closer to 12,000 not 9,000. I cover around 15,000 miles a year in my daily drive Alfa Mito (which I think may be coming to the US in a year or two), and is very much the city car you are referring too.

One thing you have not mentioned is that actually many small city cars are great fun to drive. Maybe not on a long boring straight road, but as soon as things get twisty they are way more chuckable than larger saloons.

On the subject of safety I would have agreed with you until Fifth Gear in the UK crash tested a Renault Modus City car against that perceived titan of safety the Volvo 740. The surprising results are on the You Tube link. http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=86M_fV-1yKY While buying the larger car is still safer a modern city car is infinitely safer than even a much larger 10 year old car.</description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>A few things, not sure where you got you stats from but I&#8217;m pretty certain average mileage in the UK is closer to 12,000 not 9,000. I cover around 15,000 miles a year in my daily drive Alfa Mito (which I think may be coming to the US in a year or two), and is very much the city car you are referring too. </p>
<p>One thing you have not mentioned is that actually many small city cars are great fun to drive. Maybe not on a long boring straight road, but as soon as things get twisty they are way more chuckable than larger saloons. </p>
<p>On the subject of safety I would have agreed with you until Fifth Gear in the UK crash tested a Renault Modus City car against that perceived titan of safety the Volvo 740. The surprising results are on the You Tube link. <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=86M_fV-1yKY" rel="nofollow">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=86M_fV-1yKY</a> While buying the larger car is still safer a modern city car is infinitely safer than even a much larger 10 year old car.</p>
